Subject: Re: [T2] Composite Drum on '71 rear?

Back off the shoes with the adjusters. There is often a lip around the edge that the shoes catch on and retains the drum. 

To check - if the drum will come off even a bit, rotate while you pull. If it gets hard to rotate while you are doing this the shoes are catching. 

Chris
'78 Westy w/Corvair implant
